ce into the vocabulary of the ongoing and primarily international debate surrounding the idea of avant-gardism, providing readers with a functional vocabulary for discussing some of the most hermetic and yet energetic literature ever produced in this country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aLiterature, ExperimentalzCanadaxHistory and criticism. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269690740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442696907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442696907.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK